Arizona State University, Northern Arizona University and the University of Arizona are coming together to ensure you and your family are well informed about the opportunities and resources available to you. As your public universities, we are working together to ensure you find your best college fit. We are excited to invite you to Tri-University Week.

We have teamed up to host joint virtual information sessions for prospective students and families to discuss the following:

How to navigate the college admission process.
Scholarships and financial aid.
Information about each university.
The honors experience at each university.

https://visit.asu.edu/tri-university

Hemos estado trabajando diligentemente en planes para reabrir las escuelas este otoño. Nuestra primera prioridad sigue siendo la salud y la seguridad de nuestros estudiantes, el personal y sus familias. Como Distrito, estamos tomando decisiones para garantizar la coherencia y la equidad en todo el distrito para nuestros estudiantes. Continuamos analizando los datos de COVID-19 y siguiendo las pólizas del CDC y el Departamento de Salud del Condado de Maricopa. Debido a la situación cambiante de COVID-19, estas opciones son tentativas y están sujetas a cambios debido a las pólizas federales y estatales para garantizar la salud y la seguridad de nuestros estudiantes, el personal y sus familias."

Tóme un momento para leer la carta completa de regreso a la escuela de la Superintendente Nora Gutiérrez a continuación.

https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_180232/site_180233/Documents/Safe-to-Return-to-School-Spanish.pdf

post_text:
Safe Return to School

We have been diligently working on plans to reopen schools this Fall. Our first priority remains the health and safety of our students, staff, and their families. As a district, we are making decisions to ensure consistency and equity districtwide for our students. We continue to look at COVID-19 data and follow guidelines from the CDC and Maricopa County Health Department.

Due to the ever-changing COVID-19 situation, the learning model options are tentative and subject to change due to federal and state guidelines to ensure the health and safety of our students, staff, and their families.

Please take a moment to read Superintendent Nora Gutierrez's entire safe return to school letter below.

https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_180232/site_180233/Documents/Safe-Return-to-School-Letter.pdf

Access ASU
May 8 at 4:01 PM ·

Happy Teacher Appreciation Week!

Before this week comes to an end, we would like to acknowledge and thank Emily Brown from Westview in the Tolleson Union High School District !

Ms. Brown teachers and coordinates Jobs for Arizona Graduates (JAG) and Academic & Career Success. Ms. Brown was born with a passion for education, she recalls always playing school at home with siblings and always volunteering to help her teachers in any way possible. Her amazing teachers were her inspiration to become an educator herself. She earned her Bachelors's in Elementary Education and then earned her Master’s Degree in School Counseling.

Westview High School is very fortunate to have her on staff. Ms. Brown also enjoys being part of Westview's PBIS and the Knights for Knights peer mediator program. She loves being able to work with students to help them plan for their future.

Thank you Emily Brown and all our amazing teachers at Tolleson Union High School District, your hard work and dedication do not go unnoticed. Happy Teacher Appreciation Week!

post_text:
Rebecca Smith is a junior and in the Early Childhood Education program at Westview High School. Currently, Rebecca serves students across the state of Arizona as the Vice President of Competitive Events for AZFCCLA. Family Career & Community Leaders of America is the Career and Technical Student Organization, or CTSO, that aligns to Culinary Arts, Early Childhood Education, and Fashion Design & Merchandising.

Rebecca recently learned she will be serving a second term as a State Officer for AZFCCLA during her senior year, although the exact office is yet to be determined.

Jeanette Neese, WHS ECE/Fashion teacher and FCCLA advisor, also serves on the State Board for FCCLA. We are proud to have both of these fine leaders representing our district at this level.

post_text: West Point High School Engineering was able to 3-D print and donate items that support Personal Protective Equipment used by local healthcare workers. Once printed the 3-dimensional parts must be sealed in Ziplock bags for a minimum of 72 hours before then can be donated. The printed mask parts are worn on the forehead and ear guards are used to preserve the backs of healthcare workers’ ears from the wear and tear that the mask straps cause. The filament used to print 3-D items can go bad if it’s not utilized in a timely manner.

post_text:
Congratulations to Sierra Linda High School on their newest addition to their campus. Sierra Linda has a brand new Performing and Fine Arts Center located near the south entrance of the school, near the gym.

We want to thank our parents and school community for supporting the project by voting a resounding “yes” during the last bond election. The official opening of the PAC has been delayed due to the school closures but once we are able to, we will have a grand celebration to highlight and showcase this wonderful new addition.

We can’t wait for our students to perform in this brand new facility! Thank you to ADM Group and McCarthy for this truly state-of-the-art facility. We know we will get great use from this performing arts center for many years to come!

post_text: TUHSD CTE doing its part to help out during the COVID-19 crisis
shared_text:
St. Joseph's Foundation
April 15 at 3:12 PM ·

THREE CHEERS to Sierra Linda High School in Tolleson Union High School District! And a big thank you to Samantha Gordon, head athletic trainer and sports medicine teacher, for dropping off PPE donated by the school to support St. Joseph’s #COVID-19 efforts. While the high school campus is closed, Gordon said administrators chose to donate supplies not being used by students participating in a medical assistant program.
PPE is urgently needed by St. Joseph’s to keep our frontline caregivers, staff and patients safe. Find out how you can help at www.supportstjosephs.org/emergencyfund
#WeNeedPPE #hellohumankindness #TUHSD #supportstjosephs #dignityhealthaz

text: Updated information including details about Meal Packs for TUHSD students

post_text:
On Wednesday, March 25, Tolleson Union High School District students can pick up a Meal Pack at the high school where they are currently enrolled. Meal Packs will be distributed from 4:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m.

Beginning Monday, March 30, Tolleson Union High School District students can receive a 5-day Meal Pack for the week. Monday Meal Packs will include breakfast and lunch for 5 days for Tolleson Union High School District students. Meals will be distributed from 4:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m. each Monday.

Tolleson Union High School District students must be present in order to receive the 5-day Meal Pack.

The Odyssey of the Mind Regional Tournament was held this past Saturday on the campus of Tolleson Union High School and University High School, and it was amazing! Over 1,400 people were on the campus with 98 teams and 43 schools from Northern to Central Arizona competing.

The Dream Team consisting of Syed, Sydrah, Zain, Jeremiah, Berzi, Anthony Le, and Sajid, scored the highest in University High School and Tolleson Union history! They will move onto the state competition on April 4th in Tucson.

Way to go and congratulations!

Access ASU
February 28 at 8:01 AM ·

Earlier this month was National School Counseling Week. In honor of the counselors who work tirelessly to prepare our #FutureSunDevils for college, we're taking the time to highlight them and the work they do throughout the month of February.

Meet Kristeena Torres. She's been a counselor for six years and is in her fourth with Sierra Linda in the Tolleson Union High School District.

Her goal is to help students find their unique path to their higher education degree so they can #thrive and find a career they truly want.

In her own words: "Remembering students as freshmen and seeing their progress when they graduate is a great feeling, knowing I had a part of their pathway to help them to get to their goals small & big."

post_text:
Project Green is University High School’s environmental and sustainability club. The club focuses on building a positive community and improving environmental awareness through gardening. Since the club’s establishment, their members have accomplished the construction and maintenance of a greenhouse and tower gardens. The club is excited to announce that they have received approval to begin a community market at Tolleson City Hall.

The upcoming dates for the community market are on Saturday, March 7th, as well as Saturday, April 4th.

• On March 7th, Project Green will be participating in the Tolleson Latin Music Festival by setting up a stand and selling produce that they've grown in their greenhouse.

• On April 4th, Project Green is inviting many local vendors to their first community market hosted at the Tolleson City Hall. Once again, Project Green will be selling produce from their greenhouse and everyone is invited!
